divs: sighting detailsi am a keen photographer but my mainstream is macro (insects). i am also a 90\10 for believing in et phenomenon. i took a few screenshots from the video below to see if i could get an outline of some sort. as a macro photographer light is always short at high magnification and i have learned to "push" some problem photos with photoshop. i was watching this video and thought i could maybe do something similar. i took 6 screenshots from various parts of the video with a screen freeze program from the internet. one of the frames is producing a "pixel shadow" which i cannot explain. during my macro work i have seen pixels light up when you go ott with the settings, but these are normally random throughout the image or if it is a reflection of a light source it usually flares. this one seems to me to have some organisation. the video is off you tube and it was broadcast by fox13 news - pasco - 14th march 2008. the link is here: http:\\uk.youtube.com\watch?v=utpayxwnmba&eurl=http:\\www.directvillasflorida.com\florida-blog\index.php\most-convincing-ufo-sightings-in-florida\ i don't know if the video is fake, real et or a man made craft. i live in the uk and i don't know who took the video. the only controls used in ps is brightness, contrast and shadow. the first frame that i have included is the actual screenshot so you can see where the progress slider is on the video where i froze the image. the second is the ps version. the refelection seems to give the craft direction with a back and front. maybe a pulse of some sort that has been picked up? as i have said i don't know how real or relevant this may be but i thought it was worth posting. the other 5 frames didn't seem to produce anything. anybody should be able to produce this with a photo program and the right video frame.
